Git add new options (#9576)

* Add git_add spec;

* Add pathspec and default parameters for git_add;

* Auto corrections from rubocop;

Frameit layout fix (#8031)

* Improved frameit layout

Fixes scaling if device frame too high (noticeable with iPad Pro screenshots), fixes #1725;
fixes vertically "jumping" device frame depending on title height (Titles with descenders such as g, y caused the device frame to be shifted downwards);
consider padding to limit the title width;

# Conflicts:
#	frameit/lib/frameit/editor.rb

* [frameit] fix wandering offset

if offsets.json specifies a width < screenshot width, the already modified offset was modified again and caused screenshots 2-5 to wander around in the frame

frameit: Added font_scale_factor as a fraction of the screen width (#8034)

* Added font_scale_factor

as a fraction of the screen width;
allows to limit the font size in order to achieve the same font size for all shots;
should fix #1728;

(feat/actions): Add new action 'check if the given git tag exists in the repo or not' (#5555)

* Add action to check whether the given tag exists or not;

* Add doc for git_tag_exists action;

* Add more specific tests for git_tag_exists_spec

* Fix rubocop offenses;

* Shell escape the tag parameter in the git command;

* Log command if verbose true;

* Replace self.details of git_tag exists with nil instead of empty array;

* Update self.output for git_tag_exists;

* Update documentation for git_tag_exists action;
